 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 3.76,
   "text": "Every 12 years, China and much of East Asia has a baby boom."
  },
  {
   "start": 4.34,
   "end": 7.92,
   "text": "Not because of the economy, not because of policy, because of the zodiac."
  },
  {
   "start": 8.4,
   "end": 10.56,
   "text": "Parents want their child born in the year of the dragon."
  },
  {
   "start": 11.04,
   "end": 15.6,
   "text": "The Chinese zodiac runs on 12 animals, one per year, and the dragon is the most prized"
  },
  {
   "start": 15.6,
   "end": 18.52,
   "text": "of them all, tied to strength, luck, ambition, success."
  },
  {
   "start": 19.02,
   "end": 21.6,
   "text": "A dragon child is seen as destined for great things."
  },
  {
   "start": 21.94,
   "end": 25.58,
   "text": "So couples actually plan around it, trying to time a birth for a dragon year."
  },
  {
   "start": 25.92,
   "end": 27.02,
   "text": "And here's the wild part."
  },
  {
   "start": 27.22,
   "end": 28.26,
   "text": "You can see it in the numbers."
  },
  {
   "start": 28.78,
   "end": 30.46,
   "text": "In dragon years, births rise."
  },
  {
   "start": 31.08,
   "end": 35.84,
   "text": "China's last full dragon year, 2012, brought a clear bump, reportedly the most births in"
  },
  {
   "start": 35.84,
   "end": 40.96,
   "text": "over a decade, and the effect is even sharper in places like Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Singapore,"
  },
  {
   "start": 41.38,
   "end": 45.16,
   "text": "where dragon years produce a visible spike, followed by a dip the very next year."
  },
  {
   "start": 45.54,
   "end": 48.5,
   "text": "A superstition, leaving a hard fingerprint on a country's demographics."
  },
  {
   "start": 49.18,
   "end": 51.1,
   "text": "There's even a catch for the dragon kids themselves."
  },
  {
   "start": 51.62,
   "end": 55.28,
   "text": "Being born in a boom year means a bigger generation, so more competition for school"
  },
  {
   "start": 55.28,
   "end": 61.42,
   "text": "places, university spots, jobs, their whole lives, a lucky sign, and a very crowded class."
  },
  {
   "start": 61.94,
   "end": 65.94,
   "text": "We tend to think of superstition as harmless, but the wish for a dragon child literally"
  },
  {
   "start": 65.94,
   "end": 69.76,
   "text": "bends the birth rate of the most populous region on earth every 12 years."
  },
  {
   "start": 70.28,
   "end": 70.86,
   "text": "Like clockwork."
  },
  {
   "start": 71.36,
   "end": 72.46,
   "text": "Want to actually start learning?"
  },
  {
   "start": 73.16,
   "end": 73.6,
   "text": "Chinese?"
  },
  {
   "start": 74.38,
   "end": 78.26,
   "text": "Discover thousands of free exercises and more learning content on stacktags.io."
  }
 ]
}